SIMPLE: passant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Passant
<hw>Pas"sant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p. pr. of
<ets>passer</ets>. See <er>Pass</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Passing from one to another; in circulation;
current.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many opinions are <qex>passant</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Cursory, careless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On a <qex>passant</qex> rewiew of what I wrote to the bishop.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir P. Pett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Surpassing; excelling.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Walking; -- said of any animal on
an escutcheon, which is represented as walking with the dexter paw
raised.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passee</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Passe</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>passe</ent>⟦br⟧
